ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[The sharp drop of WNV cases during the current season compared to the 2
previous ones, in 2000 and 2001, is indeed striking. Comments, ideas will
be welcomed.
The recently discovered diurnal mosquito is _Aedes caspius_ . The MOH has
now issued new guidelines advising inhabitants of the relevant locations to
take the appropriate preventive measures during the day as well - Mod.AS]
